Subject: [PATCH 147/174] =?UTF-8?q?elf:=20ELF=5FEXEC=5FPAGESIZE=20=3D=20MM?=
 =?UTF-8?q?UPAGE=5FSIZE=20=E2=80=94=20AT=5FPAGESZ=20is=20the=20hardware=20?=
 =?UTF-8?q?page?=
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

ELF_EXEC_PAGESIZE feeds AT_PAGESZ, the page size the kernel advertises to
userspace.  Userspace (libc, ld.so) drives all of its own stack/mmap/mprotect
alignment from it, so under page clustering it MUST equal the hardware page
(MMUPAGE_SIZE), never the kernel's internal clustered PAGE_SIZE.  Otherwise
the kernel lays out the user stack in one granularity while userspace computes
addresses in another — the exec-time user-stack desync class.

Three arches defined it as PAGE_SIZE, which scales with the clustered page and
would advertise e.g. 64 KB to a userspace running on 4 KB hardware pages once
PGCL is enabled there:

  arch/arc, arch/hexagon, arch/xtensa:  PAGE_SIZE -> MMUPAGE_SIZE

Two more hardcoded the literal hardware-page size; switch them to the named
invariant so it is correct by construction rather than by luck (both arches
have a fixed, non-configurable page size, so this is identical at every
PAGE_MMUSHIFT, including 0):

  arch/arm   (4096) -> MMUPAGE_SIZE
  arch/alpha (8192) -> MMUPAGE_SIZE

Deliberately NOT touched, to stay byte-identical to mainline at every config
(Newton limit):
  - parisc: page size is user-configurable (PARISC_PAGE_SIZE_4KB/16KB/64KB);
    the 4096 literal already diverges from the hardware page at 16/64 KB, so
    converting would change behaviour for those (separate, pre-existing issue).
  - m68k: page size is platform-selected (SUN3/COLDFIRE => 8 KB else 4 KB) via
    a conditional that cannot be guaranteed equal to MMUPAGE_SIZE on every
    variant.
  - microblaze: ELF_EXEC_PAGESIZE lives in uapi/asm/elf.h, where the
    kernel-internal MMUPAGE_SIZE is not available; its 4096 already equals the
    fixed hardware page.

MMUPAGE_SIZE is co-defined with PAGE_SIZE in include/vdso/page.h, so it is in
scope wherever PAGE_SIZE was.  Identity at PAGE_MMUSHIFT==0.  Compile-verified
fs/binfmt_elf.o on arm and alpha at PAGE_MMUSHIFT=4 and on arc and xtensa at
their default configs.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 <noreply@anthropic.com>
